    "short_description": "A form of embroidery from Bengal often used to stitch together old saris to make quilts (Nakshi Kantha).",
    "long_description": "Kantha is one of the oldest forms of embroidery originating from India. Its origins trace back to the ancient pre-Vedic ages. Traditionally, old sarees and dhotis were stacked on each other and hand-stitched to make a thin piece of cushion or quilt (Kantha). \n\nThe entire cloth is covered with running stitches, employing beautiful motifs of flowers, animals, birds and geometrical shapes. Today, it is done on new fabrics like tussar silk and cotton for commercial products.",
